.TH BARE 1 "April 2026" "bare 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bare \- interactive shell in x86_64 Linux assembly
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bare
[\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-login\fR]
[\fB\-c\fR \fIcommand\fR]
[\fB\-\-bench\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bare
is an interactive shell written entirely in x86_64 Linux assembly.
No libc, no runtime, pure syscalls. Single static binary.
.PP
Pure syscalls, zero overhead. No interpreter, no runtime, no garbage
collector. Just your keystrokes and the kernel.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-login
Login shell mode. Sources \fI~/.bare_profile\fR on startup.
.TP
.B \-c \fIcommand\fR
Execute \fIcommand\fR and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-bench
Print startup time in microseconds and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.TP
.B TAB / Shift\-TAB
Interactive completion cycling with LS_COLORS.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-R
Reverse incremental history search.
.TP
.B Up / Down
History navigation. With typed prefix, filters matching entries.
.TP
.B Alt\-F / Alt\-B
Move cursor forward/backward by word.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-A / Ctrl\-E
Move to beginning/end of line.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-K / Ctrl\-U / Ctrl\-W
Kill to end / clear line / delete word backward.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-L
Clear screen.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-C
Clear current line.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Z
Suspend foreground process.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-G
Edit current line in $EDITOR.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Y
Copy line to clipboard (xclip).
.TP
.B Ctrl\-D
Exit (on empty line).
.SH COLON COMMANDS
.TP
.B :nick \fR[\fIname = value\fR | \fI\-name\fR]
Command aliases.
.TP
.B :gnick \fR[\fIname = value\fR | \fI\-name\fR]
Global aliases (expand anywhere in line).
.TP
.B :abbrev \fR[\fIname = value\fR | \fI\-name\fR]
Abbreviations (expand on space).
.TP
.B :bm \fR[\fIname\fR [\fIpath\fR] [\fI#tags\fR]]
Bookmarks. \fB:bm ?tag\fR to search.
.TP
.B :dirs
Directory history. \fBcd N\fR to jump to entry N.
.TP
.B :theme \fR[\fIname\fR]
Color themes: default, solarized, dracula, gruvbox, nord, monokai.
.TP
.B :config \fR[\fIkey\fR [\fIvalue\fR]]
View or change configuration.
.TP
.B :calc \fIexpression\fR
Integer calculator (+, \-, *, /, %).
.TP
.B :stats
Command frequency analysis from history.
.TP
.B :validate \fIpattern\fR = \fIaction\fR
Safety rules (warn, confirm, block).
.TP
.B :save_session / :load_session / :list_sessions
Session management.
.TP
.B :jobs / :fg \fR[\fIN\fR] / :bg \fR[\fIN\fR]
Job control.
.TP
.B :env \fR[\fIVAR\fR | set \fIVAR val\fR | unset \fIVAR\fR]
Environment management.
.TP
.B :reload
Reload ~/.barerc configuration.
.TP
.B :info / :version / :help
Shell information.
.SH PLUGINS
Plugins are executables in \fI~/.bare/plugins/\fR. Any unknown colon
command runs the matching plugin with remaining arguments.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.barerc
Configuration file (auto\-saved on exit).
.TP
.I ~/.bare_profile
Login profile (sourced with \-l flag). Simple export lines only.
.TP
.I ~/.bare_history
Command history (capped at 1000 entries).
.TP
.I ~/.bare/plugins/
Plugin directory.
.TP
.I ~/.bare/sessions/
Saved sessions.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Settings in ~/.barerc use \fIkey = value\fR format:
.PP
.nf
nick.ls = ls \-\-color \-F
gnick.G = | grep
abbrev.gst = git status
bm.home = /home/user
c_prompt = 208
show_tips = false
auto_pair = true
rprompt = true
history_dedup = smart
.fi
.SH PART OF
CHasm (CHange to ASM) suite.
